RoboQ Changelog
===============

All notable changes to the RoboQ quiz-generation pipeline are recorded here.
Dates are in YYYY-MM-DD format.


[2026-04-15] Phase 1: Logic & Reasoning Upgrade
------------------------------------------------

Added
~~~~~
* Semantic router (gpt-4o-mini) that inspects the first ~300 characters of
  the parsed document and classifies it as LOGIC_BASED or MEMORIZATION_BASED
  using langchain `.with_structured_output(RouteDecision)`.
  See script.py::build_router.
* Branch B — logic pipeline (gpt-4o), implemented as an LCEL chain:
    1. Procedural abstraction sub-chain that extracts theorems, formulas,
       procedural rules, and common pitfalls from a chunk.
    2. CoT + few-shot generation sub-chain with three in-context examples
       (calculus chain rule, kinetic energy, binary-search complexity).
    3. Pydantic-enforced structured output via
       `.with_structured_output(QuizOutput)`.
  See script.py::build_logic_chain.
* Pydantic schemas: `RouteDecision`, `LogicQuestion` (with a `reasoning`
  field that forces Chain-of-Thought before the question fields), and
  `QuizOutput`. See script.py lines 43–78.
* Asynchronous chunk fan-out with `asyncio.gather` so gpt-4o + CoT latency
  is amortized across chunks. See script.py::_generate_for_document_async.
* Per-chunk fallback from the logic branch to the memorization branch on
  token-limit or any other logic-branch exception, so no chunk is dropped.
  See script.py::run_logic_branch and _is_token_limit_error.
* Router-level fallback: if classification itself fails, the document
  defaults to the memorization branch.
* `reasoning` field is logged to stdout and stripped from the response
  before it reaches the frontend, keeping the UI contract unchanged.
  See script.py::_normalize_question.
* CHANGELOG file (this file).

Changed
~~~~~~~
* script.py rewritten around the router + two-branch architecture. Public
  entry point `generate_questions(file_path, pagenum)` keeps the exact same
  signature and return shape, so app.py needs zero changes.
* Branch A — memorization pipeline — still uses
  `load_summarize_chain(chain_type="refine")` on gpt-4o-mini and the
  existing free-form JSON cleaner, now wrapped in an async helper
  (`run_memorization_branch`) so it composes with the orchestration layer.
* README rewritten to document the Phase 1 architecture, list the two
  required model entitlements (gpt-4o-mini and gpt-4o), and renumber the
  run steps.
* requirements.txt now pins `langchain-core` and `pydantic>=2` explicitly
  (previously pulled in transitively).

Notes
~~~~~
* The OpenAI API key in .env must have access to BOTH gpt-4o-mini (router +
  memorization branch) and gpt-4o (logic branch).
* .env is not committed — configure it locally per the README.


[2025 and earlier] Pre-Phase-1 baseline
---------------------------------------

* Flask web app (app.py) that accepts PDF uploads, renders per-page
  thumbnails with PyMuPDF, and generates a quiz for the selected page.
* Single quiz-generation path: `load_summarize_chain(chain_type="refine")`
  on gpt-4o-mini driven by a hand-written AP-style prompt, with regex-based
  JSON cleanup and option shuffling.
* No routing, no structured output, no async, no CoT.
